servings: 2
time required: 2 hours 20 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position (top and middle positions for 8 servings) and preheat #oven{} to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Pat @chicken cutlets{20%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

In a #medium bowl{}, whisk together @BBQ sauce{3/4%cup}, @brown sugar{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, half the @white wine vinegar{5%teaspoon} (you'll use the rest in Step 3), salt, and pepper.

Place chicken in a 5- to 6-quart #slow cooker{}; pour BBQ sauce mixture over top. Cook on high until cooked through and tender, ~{1 1/2%hours}.

Once chicken has cooked for 1 1/2 hours, transfer to a #large bowl{}. Using two #forks{}, shred chicken.

> TIP: You can shred chicken directly in slow cooker, but be careful—it's hot!

Return shredded chicken to slow cooker and stir to combine. Cover and cook for ~{30%minutes} more. Taste and season with salt and pepper if desired.

== Potato Wedges ==

After returning chicken to slow cooker, cut @potatoes{24%ounce} into ¼-inch-thick wedges; toss on a #baking sheet{} (divide between two sheets for 8 servings) with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon}, @fry seasoning{2%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> For 8 servings, roast on top and middle racks, swapping rack positions halfway through.

== Cabbage Slaw ==

In a second large bowl, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, @shredded carrots{4%ounce}, @mayonnaise{4%tablespoon}, remaining vinegar, @sugar{1%teaspoon} (2 tsp for 8), salt, and pepper.

== Assembly ==

Toast @brioche buns{4} in #oven{} until golden.

Divide saucy chicken between buns and top with as much slaw as you like. Serve with potato wedges and any remaining slaw on the side.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.